###############################################################################
#ADIOS VERSION of FLEXWIN
#BUG REPORT: lei@princeton.edu

#############################################################
#Pre-request
1. SAC(libary)
2. mpicc
3. mpif90

#############################################################
#modify the input and output
1. open "FLEXWIN_ASDF-V2.1" and open file "FLEXWIN_ADIOS.f90"
2. the input file is defined in "input_fn" variables
3. the output direcotry is defined in "outdir" variables

#############################################################
#compile the code
1. run: make clean
2. run: make
3. the excutable file "WORKFLOW" is generated

#############################################################
#To test the code
1. open "parallel.sh", in line 5, you see "cd /tigress/lei/test/FLEXWIN_ASDF-V2.1. modify it with your own direcotry. You can also specify the processor number.
2. use "qsub parallel.sh" to submit the job
3. the output file should be in "./output" direcotry. The number of output file should be the same with the number of processor. 


#############################################################
#some tips:
1. if you want to use you own data, you can modify the script "run_input_cmt.csh" to generate your own filelist and then modify the input file in "FLEXWIN_ADIOS.f90".


